MOSCOW â€“ Investors from Britain bought almost 50% of Polyus shares sold by the gold producer's controlling shareholder, according to deal bookrunner VTB Capital. Polyus said on Thursday that its controlling shareholder, Polyus Gold International Ltd (PGIL), had sold a 3.84% stake in the company via an accelerated bookbuilding (ABB). Russian investors bought about a third of the other half, while the remaining shares were acquired by investors from Europe, the United States and Asia, said Boris Kvasov, co-head of equity capital markets at VTB Capital.